Newly elected chairman of Bebeji Local Government Area, Alhaji Ali Namadi has been reported dead two days after winning the polls.  Mr. Namadi was among the successful APC chairmanship candidates in the just concluded local government councils elections held on Saturday 16th January, 2021. Alhaji Ibrahim Adamu Tiga, Director Campaign to the late chairman in a terse statement that was made available to reporters in Kano said Namadi died by 1:00 am on Tuesday after a brief illness. Mr Tiga explained that the late Chairman drove himself to Bebeji General Hospital for medical attention before he gave up the ghost. Tiga disclosed that baring any last minute change, Namadi’s funeral prayers would take place in his hometown, Bebeji, this morning. Source By Abbas Bamalli Kano - The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) candidate, Alhaji Aliyu Datti-Yako as the winner of the re-run election for Kiru/Bebeji Federal Constituency of Kano State. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the PDP candidate, Alhaji Aliyu Datti-Yako defeated… January 26, 2020 In "Politics" From Kolade Adeyemi Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Alhaji Aliyu Datti Yako of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP), has been declared winner of the Kiru/Bebeji Federal Constituency rerun election in Kano state. Yako, defeated the controversial former chairman on appropriation and proponent of “Budget Padding” Abdulmumuni Jibrin Kofa of the All… January 26, 2020 In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Federal lawmaker representing Bebeji/Kiru Federal Constituency of Kano State at the green chamber, Hon Abdulmumin Jibrin has been suspended by the Bebeji Local Government chapter of the All Progressive Congress, APC, over alleged anti-party activities. His suspension which  was contained in a statement… August 1, 2019 In "Top Stories"